      "content": "I hear you on the national identity thing, but for someone actually sending staff into the field, that sounds a bit vague. When you say \"episodic and situational,\" are you saying that instability is basically the norm whenever politics or resources get tight? Like, is it fair to assume that ethnic loyalty always trumps national identity when things get difficult? I'm trying to gauge if we're looking at a place where these deep-seated tribal divides are just an inevitable part of the social fabric.",
